title: Product Growth
summary:
I always believe in going the extra mile, diving deep to tackle problems at their roots rather than just skimming the surface. 

My diverse skills span interpersonal communication, technical prowess, and business intelligence across various fields. I excel at bridging gaps in cross-regional and cross-industry communication. As someone who values lifelong learning, I stay curious and open, always ready to embrace and adapt to new ideas and opportunities that arise.

Outside of work, gaming has been a passion of mine since childhood. I enjoy a wide range of games on various platforms, with current favorites including Genshin Impact, Stellar Blade, and Hell Diver 2. When I'm not gaming, you can find me skiing down powdery slopes, or cheering on my favorite sports teams: Liverpool FC, the Toronto Blue Jays, and the Maple Leafs.

name: Ada Liu

title: Business Development
titleDescription:
At Blueberry AI, I’m part of a mission to redefine how enterprises manage their digital assets—because your content deserves better than chaos. From our Silicon Valley roots to our hubs in Chengdu and Shanghai, we’re building smarter, faster, and downright revolutionary solutions for the modern workplace.

Our AI-powered platform is like having a genius librarian for your digital world. Need that critical file yesterday? We’ve got you covered with blazing-fast previews, AI smart search, and auto-tagging that feels like magic. No more digging through folders or wrangling complex workflows—just effortless organization and collaboration at your fingertips.

I’m here because I love seeing businesses unlock their potential with game-changing tech. At Blueberry AI, we’re not just about managing assets; we’re about helping you work smarter, dream bigger, and achieve more. Let’s connect and see how we can shake up the future of work together!
name: Nicholas Harris

title: Fractional CMO
summary: As a Growth Marketing leader I have decade of experience managing business accounts with monthly spend ranging from $100K to $55M in monthly spend, serving both B2B and B2C, focusing on both acquisition and retention. Recently, I led ecommerce and acquisition efforts in the mobile app space in a high growth environment, utilizing all digital channels including SEM, SEO, programmatic display, social, affiliate, referral TV and OOH. Prior to that, I led performance marketing at Macy's, where I emphasized ROI and efficiency, utilizing a dedicated MarTech team to adopt new channels and reach incremental growth. At both Macy's and gopuff, I managed teams of over 15 performance marketers, analysts, product managers, and creatives, fostering structured efficiency and personal growth. My passion lies in building and growing teams, and utilizing technology and data in marketing strategies for campaign management, measurement, creative content, awareness and user flow. As the digital marketing space evolves, I aim to bring nimble and knowledgeable leadership to build tomorrow's best practices into any role I take on.
